\f0\fs24  directory with code that calls Cloudflare\'92s AI API and external AI services{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/JW-Flo/Project-Ignite/blob/bcc8b784cac1d7962ed21c17e65e0b28a3998130/ai-orchestrator/index.js#L11-L19"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 github.com}}{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/JW-Flo/Project-Ignite/blob/bcc8b784cac1d7962ed21c17e65e0b28a3998130/ai-orchestrator/index.js#L41-L50"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 github.com}}. This implies an AI orchestrator worker is meant to be deployed. Its config should be checked (it might be using the main wrangler\'92s 
\f2\fs26 [env.ai]
\f0\fs24  or have its own). Ensure environment variables like 
\f2\fs26 AI_GATEWAY_TOKEN
\f0\fs24 , 
\f2\fs26 AI_PROVIDER
\f0\fs24  etc., are set if needed. The AI worker is part of the autonomous system (handling tasks like documentation generation or code suggestions), so while not a focus of the original question, it is a component to include in the cleanup plan for completeness. Currently, the AI config looks mostly in order but make sure the route domain is corrected (like others) and that any secrets (API keys for AI services) are securely stored.\
