\f0\fs24  in the HTML{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/JW-Flo/Project-Ignite/blob/bcc8b784cac1d7962ed21c17e65e0b28a3998130/mcp-mobile/index.js#L184-L193"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 github.com}} \'96 meaning it\'92s injecting the secret into client-side JS. 
\f1\b This is a security risk
\f0\b0 , since it exposes the client secret publicly. A better design is to handle admin login differently (see point 5 below). In the interim, ensure this value is something appropriately secure even if exposed.\
